# Documentation style (`docs/`)

Same voice as the always-on `project-conventions.mdc` rule (British English, no emojis).

## Voice and format

- Prefer **links to source paths** over pasting long code; line numbers drift.

## When behaviour changes

- If the change reflects a **trade-off** or **reverses** a prior assumption, add at least a short paragraph to `docs/decisions.md`.

## Plans vs maintained docs

- `.cursor/plans/` is **design-time** material. When behaviour is normative for contributors, document it under `docs/` (and `README.md` if user-facing).
